post_text:
Hello Everyone,

If you have not applied for the P-EBT benefits, please contact the school for more information including the application link. All students in our district and younger siblings in the family are eligible to receive this benefit because we participate in the Community Eligibility Provision (CEP) program. All our students receive free breakfast and lunch so they qualify for the one time benefit of $285 per child. Parents / Guardians must complete the short application to receive the benefits.

The application deadline has been extended to August 21st.

Eligible families that received SNAP benefits for March have already received P-EBT benefits and do not have to apply. If you need help filling out the P-EBT application, please contact the P-EBT Call Center at 833-613-6220. The public charge rule does not apply to P-EBT benefits.

post_text:
March 31, 2020

As per Governor Abbott's the announcement this afternoon regarding all schools in Texas, WSISD will be closed through May 4, 2020.

Lessons will continue to be distributed and picked up. Drop-off on April 3rd will be the same.

An updated schedule for meals and lessons will be posted in businesses in town by tomorrow.

Texas Dept of Agriculture has changed the guidelines for serving meals after March 31. The changes include:

1. Meals may not be provided for weekends and school holidays.

2.Children who are not enrolled in WSISD must be present to be provided a meal.

We will serve on Friday, April 3rd. The meals will include: Lunch for April 3 and April 6; Breakfast for April 6 and April 7.

As per UIL previous announcement, there will be no UIL contests held until May 4th, 2020.

Please check the school website walnutspringsisd.net for the most up to date information. Stay safe and healthy.

post_text:
Both Junior High Hornet teams added another victory to their season record with a pair of wins over the Kopperl Eagles in Kopperl on Thursday, January 30th. The girls defeated the Lady Eagles by a score of 19 to 5.Sixth grader, Alleigh Ortega, led all scorers with her 11 points. Emmalou Aleman added 4 points and America Pardo and Lupe Favela had 2 points each.

The Junior High boys remained undefeated in district play with a 36 to 14 win over the Eagles. Bryan Chavez led the Hornets with his 12 points. Diego Muniz had 7 points with D'Marcus finishing the game with 6 points as well as Santos Pina who also had six points. Brenden Shuemake had 3 points and Jesse Lamb and Dawson Gomez scored 2 points each.

The Hornets will close out the 2019-2020 basketball season when they travel to Morgan on February 3 for a 5:30 girl's game followed by the boys at 6:30.

post_text:
The Junior High boys remain undefeated running away from the Kopperl Eagles by a score of 30 to 8. Josue Muniz was the leading scorer for the Hornets with his 9 points. Bryan Chavez added 6 points with J.D. Campos scoring 5 points. Diego Muniz had 4 points, Dawson Gomez had 2 and Angel Salgado had 4.

The boys should be commended on their team play. Everyone worked hard and selflessly to make sure that Angel got on the scoreboard. Several players turned down easy baskets to make passes to assist Angel in scoring his four points. It was a great display of teamwork and camaraderie that you don't often see displayed in this day and time. Great job boys, we are proud of you.

The Hornets will play the Oglesby Tigers on Saturday to determine which team will advance to the championship game Saturday afternoon.

Everyone needs to come out and support the home teams. The tournament begins at 9:00 AM and continues throughout the day. The championship games are scheduled to be played at 3:00 and 4:00 in the afternoon.

The Lady Hornets had been struggling on offense but playing great defense over the past three games. The young ladies held the Lady Eagles to 2 points while the offense was hitting on all cylinders as the girls scored 22 points. Sofia Chavez led all scorers with her 6 points followed by Guadalupe Favela, Emmalou Aleman, and America Pardo with 4 points each. Alleigh Ortega closed out the scoring for the Lady Hornets with her two points. The ladies will play Iredell on Saturday to determine if they will play for the championship or third place.

post_text:
How 'Bout Them Hornets!! The JH girls and boys extended their win streaks with a victory over the visiting Bobcats from Blum, Monday evening, January 13.

The Lady Hornets took a commanding lead of 10-2 at halftime and went on the win the game by a score of 16-7. Sofia Chavez and Alleigh Ortega led the Hornets with 6 points each. Emma-Lou Aleman added 4 points for the Lady Hornets.

The Blum boys who were undefeated on the season challenged the Hornets who were only able to build a 13-10 halftime lead before pulling away in the third quarter to win by a score of 35-24 and protect their undefeated season.

Diego Muniz led all scorers with his 13 points. Josue Ontiveros had 7 points followed closely by Brenden Shuemake with 6. Cameron Mitchell had 4, D'Marcus Garcia had 3, and Bryan Chavez added 3.

The Hornets travel to Covington on Saturday, January 18 for a one day tournament and will open play against the Kopperl Eagles.

post_text:
The Junior High Hornets closed out their football season on Thursday, November 7th with a hard-fought 27-21 victory over the visiting Cranfills Gap Lions. The win gave the young Hornets an undefeated district record and an overall record of 8 wins and one loss.

The Hornets never trailed in the game but with 45 seconds left, the Lions scored and the game was tied 21 to 21.

On the first play following the Lion's score, Diego Muniz scored on a 55 yard run. The PAT was no good setting the Lions up to possibly winning the game. The Lions moved the ball down the field on two pass plays before Bryan Chavez made a big hit on the Gap receiver thus insuring the Hornet victory.

The Junior High Hornets team was made up of 8th Graders:
Adrian Chavez, Luis Fraire, Brenden Shuemake, Burl Vara, Diego Muniz, Santos Pina, Bryan Chavez, and Jase Strickland.

7th Grade team members included:
Jesse Lamb, Jacob Malhis, Angel Muniz, Angel Salgado, Dawson Gomez, and Josue Muniz.

post_text:
The Junior High Hornets opened their district competition against the Kopperl Eagles on October 17. The Hornets came away with a 37-0 victory. Everyone saw playing time and everyone contributed to the win.

Diego Muniz set the tone of the game when he scored on 45 yard touchdown on the opening kickoff. He then passed to Jesse Lamb for the extra point.

Muniz would score two more times before half on a 43 yard run and a 50 yard run. He passed to Santos Pina for one extra point.

Adrain Chavez scored the Hornet's next touchdown on a 41 yard run and Muniz passed to Lamb again for the PAT.

Brenden Shuemake scored the last touchdown for the Hornets on a five yard run which Muniz kicking the PAT for the Hornets.

Burl Vara and Santos Pina played great defense against the Eagles who had a large running back that was used on a regular basis throughout the game.

The Hornets play the visiting Iredell Dragons on Thursday October 24th at 6:00.

post_text:
The Junior High Hornets evened their season record to 1-1 last Thursday, September 19th when they defeated the Avalon Eagles 57 to 39. They were defeated by the Gordon Longhorns in their first game, 40-33.

Diego Muniz led the Hornets against the Longhorns scoring on a kickoff return, an interception, a 60 yard run and a 50 yard TD reception from Bryan Chavez. Jesse Lamb had a TD run and Burl Vara scored the extra point. Chavez also passed to Jase Strickland for another point after touchdown.

In the Avalon game, Bryan Chavez and Diego Muniz led the Hornets in scoring. Chavez had four touchdowns and passed for another touchdown. Muniz had a touchdown run and caught one of Chavez's passes for another. Brenden Shuemake had an interception that stalled an Avalon drive.

The Hornets travel to Covington to take on the Owls on Thursday, September 26 at 6:00.

Other members of the Hornets include 7th graders, Jacob Malhis, Angel Muniz, Angel Salgado, Dawson Gomez, and Josue Muniz. Eighth graders include Tryntin Parnell, Adrian Chavez, Luis Fraire, Blake Glass, and Santos Pina.

post_text:
Hello Everyone,

Please join us this Friday, November 9th as the
students of Walnut Springs ISD honor our Veterans.

The program will begin at 10:30 a.m. in the school auditorium.

The students will sing songs, recite poems and share quotes in tribute to our veterans.

The High School band will also perform patriotic songs.

The Gifted and Talented students have created a photo montage.

Following the program, members of the WSISD Student Council will serve our veterans a delicious lunch of various types of soups, beans and cornbread prepared by several members of the Walnut Springs Historical Association.

Veterans and their family members are encouraged to attend so we can express our gratitude for their service to this great nation.

Hope to see you there!

Hello Everyone,

We hope you are having a great summer vacation. Just sending out a few notes and reminders today.

Juniors or Seniors who want to take dual credit courses during the 2017-2018 school year must take and pass the TSI exam. This test is administered on our campus and at no cost to our students. If you are interested, please contact Mrs. Halbert at 254-797-2132 to make an appointment. The TSI exam must be completed no later than August 31, 2017.

First day of school will be Monday, August 28th. The school day will start at 7:50 am and end at 3:34 pm.

Hornet Football will start on Friday, August 18th with a scrimmage against Bynum. It is a home game so please come out and support the Hornets!!

Please check the page for updates. We will be posting new activities and important dates as they are scheduled.

See you soon!😀

Hello everyone!! This last week is going by so quickly!!
First, a big thank you to all the parents/community members who have posted pics for the yearbook staff to use. You are awesome.
Second, please remember that tomorrow is Kindergarten graduation and Elementary awards. It starts at 9 am in the auditorium.
Next, Junior High will be having a graduation ceremony and awards on Thursday, May 26th at 6 pm in the auditorium.
Finally, please come out on May 27th at 7 pm and join us in celebrating the accomplishments of this year's graduating seniors and saying our final farewells.
It has been a great year. A big thank you to all who made it possible!!
